Aggregate Functions in Insight Builder

The aggregate function performs a calculation on a set of values in Data Cloud and returns a single value.

To build the insight for aggregating the quantity by-product IDs, perform the following steps:

In the visual insight builder, select the dataset or object on which the SQL must be run.
To select the Aggregate functions, click the + icon.
Select your desired functions in the measures tab.
Select the dimension (Product ID) to group By.
Save the expression.
EXAMPLE

Consider a scenario where you want to check the total quantity of products orders using the sales order data. Use the following sample Demo DMO as a reference object.

ORDERID	PRODUCTID	QUANTITY
13131	3131	23

To build the CI for aggregating the Quantity by-product IDs, perform the following steps:

In the visual insight builder, select the dataset on which the SQL must be run.
To select the Aggregate functions, click the + icon.
In the Measures tab, select the SUM function and select the measure (Quantity) on which aggregate must be applied.
Select the dimension (Product ID) to group By.
Save the expression.

The preceding visual builder CI returns results corresponding to the following SQL expression defined:

SELECT ProductID, SUM(Quantity)
FROM OrderDetails
Group by ProductID
